HEADWORD: Corpulent
<hw>Cor"pu*lent</hw> <pr>(-p?-l<it>e</it>nt)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>corpulentus</ets>, fr. <ets>corpus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>corpulent</ets>. See <er>Corpse</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Very
fat; obese.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Solid; gross; opaque.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Stout; fleshy; bulky; obese. See
<er>Stout</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Corpulently</ent>⟦br⟧
